The paper proposes a protocol for a community of users to interact with each other while limiting the damage done by malicious or incompetent users. This involves decision-making and reputation systems, which are common topics in game theory (cs.GT), cryptography (cs.CR), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses collaborative filtering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI).
